<hr data-start=3D"895" data-end=3D"898">
<h3 data-start=3D"900" data-end=3D"932">=F0=9F=94=B9 Key Points about <code=
 data-start=3D"924" data-end=3D"931">throw</code>:</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"933" data-end=3D"1281">
<li data-start=3D"933" data-end=3D"1087">
<p data-start=3D"935" data-end=3D"1087">You can throw almost <strong data-s=
tart=3D"956" data-end=3D"968">anything</strong> (int, string, custom class,=
 etc.), but best practice is to throw <strong data-start=3D"1034" data-end=
=3D"1084">exceptions (std::exception or derived classes)</strong>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1088" data-end=3D"1208">
<p data-start=3D"1090" data-end=3D"1208">When <code data-start=3D"1095" dat=
a-end=3D"1102">throw</code> executes, normal program flow <strong data-star=
t=3D"1133" data-end=3D"1154">stops immediately</strong>, and control jumps =
to the nearest matching <code data-start=3D"1198" data-end=3D"1205">catch</=
code>.</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1209" data-end=3D"1281">
<p data-start=3D"1211" data-end=3D"1281">If no <code data-start=3D"1217" da=
ta-end=3D"1224">catch</code> matches, the program calls <code data-start=3D=
"1252" data-end=3D"1270">std::terminate()</code> and exits.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<hr data-start=3D"1283" data-end=3D"1286">
<p data-start=3D"1288" data-end=3D"1393">=F0=9F=91=89 In short:<br data-sta=
rt=3D"1300" data-end=3D"1303">
<code data-start=3D"1303" data-end=3D"1310">throw</code> =3D "Something wen=
t wrong, I can=E2=80=99t handle it here. Let someone else deal with it."</p=
>
