<hr data-start=3D"1060" data-end=3D"1063">
<h3 data-start=3D"1065" data-end=3D"1112">=F0=9F=94=B9 Why use <code data-s=
tart=3D"1080" data-end=3D"1098">invalid_argument</code> (or similar)?</h3>
<ul data-start=3D"1113" data-end=3D"1288">
<li data-start=3D"1113" data-end=3D"1182">
<p data-start=3D"1115" data-end=3D"1182">It=E2=80=99s part of <strong data-=
start=3D"1128" data-end=3D"1158"><code data-start=3D"1130" data-end=3D"1146=
">std::exception</code> hierarchy</strong> =E2=86=92 safer and standard.</p=
>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1183" data-end=3D"1242">
<p data-start=3D"1185" data-end=3D"1242">It carries a descriptive message (=
<code data-start=3D"1219" data-end=3D"1229">e.what()</code> gives it).</p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1243" data-end=3D"1288">
<p data-start=3D"1245" data-end=3D"1288">Makes debugging &amp; error handli=
ng cleaner.</p>
</li>
</ul>
<p data-start=3D"1290" data-end=3D"1310">Common ones include:</p>
<ul data-start=3D"1311" data-end=3D"1382">
<li data-start=3D"1311" data-end=3D"1331">
<p data-start=3D"1313" data-end=3D"1331"><code data-start=3D"1313" data-end=
=3D"1331">invalid_argument</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1332" data-end=3D"1348">
<p data-start=3D"1334" data-end=3D"1348"><code data-start=3D"1334" data-end=
=3D"1348">out_of_range</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1349" data-end=3D"1366">
<p data-start=3D"1351" data-end=3D"1366"><code data-start=3D"1351" data-end=
=3D"1366">runtime_error</code></p>
</li>
<li data-start=3D"1367" data-end=3D"1382">
<p data-start=3D"1369" data-end=3D"1382"><code data-start=3D"1369" data-end=
=3D"1382">logic_error</code></p>
</li>
</ul>
